  "educationalNotes": "Osmium is densest element known - 22.6 g/cm³ (dense as lead plus 25%!)! One cubic inch of osmium weighs 13 pounds. Osmium tetroxide used in biological electron microscopy. Osmium-platinum alloys extremely hard. Osmium has highest melting point with rhenium. Discovered in 1803. Named from Greek 'osme' (smell) - OsO₄ smells terrible. Toxic element - poisonous fumes. Rare and expensive."
